meanings.definition: To exceed in number or amount.
meanings.sent1: In the race, the blue car outcounts the red one.
meanings.sent2: She always outcounts her classmates in math problems.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outcounts the birds when gathering nuts.
meanings.sent4: His dedication outcounts his lack of experience.
meanings.sent5: The sun outcounts the stars in brightness.

meanings.definition: To surpass in counting or tallying.
meanings.sent1: The new machine outcounts the old one in efficiency.
meanings.sent2: Her speed in typing outcounts everyone else in the office.
meanings.sent3: The cat outcounts the dog in catching mice.
meanings.sent4: His determination outcounts his fear of failure.
meanings.sent5: The champion boxer outcounts his opponents in skill.
